Variation
. Another long specimen (LACM 7609) was inside a tube made of a proteinaceous material with cemented sediment particles (
Fig. 36A, B
), but it is unknown if it was made by the polychaete itself. There are four chaetae per parapodia, one falcate acicular and one capillary per ramus along anterior chaetigers (
Fig. 36C
). Neu- ropodia has more chaetae in posterior chaetigers with up to three aciculars and 2–3 capillaries per side (
Fig. 36D
), and in the posterior end these neurochaetae decrease their number (
Fig. 36E
) as along the anterior region, and they are not always golden or brownish.
